<div dir="ltr">Thank you Jeff. I guess there is no Java binding for this function.</div><div class="gmail_extra"><br><div class="gmail_quote">On Tue, Jan 6, 2015 at 4:37 PM, Jeff Squyres (jsquyres) <span dir="ltr">&lt;<a href="mailto:jsquyres@cisco.com" target="_blank">jsquyres@cisco.com</a>&gt;</span> wrote:<br><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin:0 0 0 .8ex;border-left:1px #ccc solid;padding-left:1ex">Sorry for the delay in answering this; this mail came after I disappeared for the US holidays.<br>
<br>
Yes -- through an Open MPI extension (you must configure Open MPI with --enable-mpi-ext=affinity or --enable-mpi-ext=all).  See:<br>
<br>
    <a href="http://www.open-mpi.org/doc/v1.8/man3/OMPI_Affinity_str.3.php" target="_blank">http://www.open-mpi.org/doc/v1.8/man3/OMPI_Affinity_str.3.php</a><br>
